One of the powers of confluence is the possibility of having an _inclusions Library where a file containing text common to a number of documents may be stored.(for example a copyright statement or company profile). This may be included in any number of documents using the {include} macro.

As far as I can see, when saving a wiki markup there is a conversion to html of the file (for display by web browsers) and the TOC is generated/rendered at this time. Any subsequent changes to headers in an included file are not picked up and displayed in the TOC until the 'including' file is re-saved.

